<MELItem itemNbr="73-31-01" id="X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.CU.MEL.2-73-31-01.1.2-73-31-01_FAA">
<Title>
<?FTID-xref 1187874.2-73-31-01_FAA?>Fuel Flow Indications</Title>
<DispatchCondition repairInterval="C" nbrInstalled="2" nbrRequired="1">
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>One may be inoperative provided:</Para>
<List listType="a.">
<ListItem>
<Para>All fuel tank quantity indications operate normally. </Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>EDTO beyond 180 minutes is not conducted.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
<Note>
<Para>Use Boeing Onboard Performance Tool (OPT) to determine take-off weight and/or landing weight as it affects aircraft performance.</Para>
</Note>
<Note rev:revStatus="R" rev:revHighlight="Add note to emphasize that cannot be simultaneously applied MEL 28-41-01 with MEL 73-31-01">
<?FTID-rev start?>
<Para>MEL 28-41-01 cannot be simultaneously applied</Para>
<?FTID-rev end?>
</Note>
</DispatchConditionRemarks>
<DispatchProcedure>
<OperationNote>
<Para>The FMC CALCULATED fuel, associated engine LEFT or RIGHT fuel used and FUEL USED total indications will be inoperative. The FUEL DISAGREE advisory message will be inoperative.</Para>
</OperationNote>
</DispatchProcedure>
</DispatchCondition>
</MELItem>
